Bovine tuberculosis, Switzerland
--------------------------------
Information received on 13 Mar 2013 from Mr Hans Wyss, chief veterinary officer, Schwarzenburgstrasse 161, Swiss Federal Veterinary Office, Liebefeld Berne, Switzerland

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 4 Mar 2013
Date of pre-confirmation of the event: 8 Mar 2013
Report date: 11 Mar 2013
Reason for notification: reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 15 Jan 2000
Manifestation of disease: subclinical infection
Causal agent: _Mycobacterium bovis_ spp. _bovis_
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to the whole country

New outbreaks (1)
Outbreak 1: Farvagny, Farvagny, Fribourg
Date of start of the outbreak: 4 Mar 2013
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 72 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 1
Affected population: one dairy cow (born in 2002) slaughtered for consumption. Suspicion of bTB at post mortem inspection. No clinical signs prior to slaughter.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 1
Total animals affected
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Cattle / 72 / 1 / 0 / 0 / 1

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: this single event does not affect the bTB-free status of Switzerland. Extensive investigations are currently running to find the source of infection and the dimension of the outbreak.

Control measures
Measures applied: quarantine, screening, disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Institute of Veterinary Bacteriology, University of Zurich (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / real-time PCR / 8 Mar 2013 / Positive

